  "lesson": {
    "title": "Diode OR Circuit",
    "description": "Press either tact button (west or east). USB splits at the cross: each path goes button → Schottky (90°, cathode toward the center) → the shared OR node → 470Ω → red LED → ground. Either input alone lights the LED; both pressed still works — a diode OR gate. Compare lesson 12 (parallel buttons without diodes). LEDs at 90° (anode north)."
